Key Match Events: Adam Zampa took 3/21 in his ten overs, scored 29 runs with the bat, and took a brilliant catch.
England were all out for 253 in 48.1 overs.
Hazlewood took the last wicket to end England's innings.
Adil Rashid hit a six off a high full-toss.
Cameron Green's trousers slipped while diving to save a boundary.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia will be without Glenn Maxwell due to a concussion injury and Mitch Marsh for personal reasons.
Marcus Stoinis and Cameron Green are the prime contenders to fill the all-rounder spots.
England have been consistently altering their lineup throughout the World Cup 2023.
England's primary concern has been their batting, having been dismissed for 170 or fewer runs in their last three matches.
England's campaign began with a nine-wicket loss to New Zealand in Ahmedabad.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed disappointment and acknowledged the team's shortcomings.
Pat Cummins praised his team's performance and highlighted their improvement.
Mitchell Starc commented on the team's momentum and Zampa's performance.
Adam Zampa reflected on his performance and the conditions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England, the defending champions, are now officially out of the World Cup.
Australia solidified their position at the points table with five wins in seven games.
